message.content: We find that $30 \cdot \frac{1}{6} = \boxed{\frac{5}{2}}$ cup of flour goes into each of the small pie crusts. Since the same total amount of flour will go into each of the large crusts, we divide $\frac{5}{2}$ by $2$ to find that $\boxed{\frac{5}{4}}$ cup of flour will go into each of the new crusts.
